==English==
===Noun===
'''formula''' (''plural'' '''formulae''' ''in scientific use'', '''formulas''' ''in informal use'')

#(''mathematics'') Any [[mathematical]] [[rule]] [[express]]ed [[symbolically]].
#:''<math>x = (-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}) / 2a</math> is the formula for finding the roots of the quadratic equation y = ax<sup>2</sup> + bx + c''.
#(''chemistry'') A [[symbolic]] [[expression]] of the [[structure]] of a [[compound]].
#:''H<sub>2</sub>O is the formula for water.''

====Synonyms====
*(''in mathematics''): mathematical formula
*(''in chemistry''): chemical formula

